            . I am a butcher, and live at Hollywell-lane. On the 16th of February, about half-past five o'clock, I saw a boy go and take a pair of shoes from Mr. Blizard's shop; I ran out and pursued the prisoner and another - I caught the prisoner in Shoreditch, and saw the shoes close by him; I cannot swear he took them.</p>
               <p>THOMAS BLIZARD. These are my shoes - I know nothing of the prisoner.</p>
